Pre-Game Insights: India and South Africa are set to face off in a Super Sunday clash at the Eden Gardens on November 5.

India has a seven-match winning streak and has already qualified for the CWC23 semis, while South Africa has scored five 300-plus team totals in this World Cup and has the most wickets in the competition.

South Africa leads the overall H2H (50 wins in 90 games) and H2H in World Cup games (three wins in five meetings). In comparison, India have triumphed in 17 of the 31 INDvSA matchups on home soil and have two wins in three ODI contests between the teams at Eden Gardens.
